{{Quote|Gormaanda is a four-star rated chef and is thrice the recipient of the Orto Culinary Academy Award for Engorgable Excellence.|An installment of Gormaanda's Culinary Corner|<ref name="hnn" />}}
The '''Orto Culinary Academy Award for Engorgable Excellence''' was awarded three times to the [[Chef/Legends|chef]] [[Gormaanda/Legends|Gormaanda]]<ref name="hnn" /> by [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].<ref name="date">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|50|life/1344_2.html|Gormaanda's Culinary Corner: Glowblue Noodles & Chav}} is set in 13:4:4 in the [[Great ReSynchronization]] dating system, which corresponds to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]] according to the reasoning [[Template:YearMathGRS|here]].</ref> Her winning was advertised in a biographical section of her column, [[Gormaanda's Culinary Corner]], which was published in the [[HoloNet News CoCo District Edition|CoCo District Edition]] of the [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]] as well as newsfeeds across the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]<ref name="hnn" /> in 22 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]].<ref name="date" /> The award shared its name with<ref name="hnn" /> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Orto/Legends|Orto]].<ref name="Orto">[[Galaxy Guide 4: Alien Races (Second Edition)|''Galaxy Guide 4: Alien Races'', Second Edition]]</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The Orto Culinary Academy Award for Engorgable Excellence was introduced in [[HoloNet News Vol. 531 50|''HoloNet News Vol. 531 #50'']], an issue of the [[HoloNet News (original website)|HoloNet News website]], which was published online<ref name="hnn" /> on [[April 4]], [[2002]].<ref name="HNN50 date">{{JCFCite|url=posts/6308795|board=Literature|thread=The Official HoloNetNews Discussion Thread|user=Mavrick889|date=2002-04-04|time=3:16 PM|archivedate=20200305125429}}</ref> The site's content was written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Paul Ens]].<ref name="Credits">{{HoloNetNewsWeb||credits.html|Credits}}</ref>

